    &lt;CommentText&gt;I attended the hospital in January for a procedure.  
I had a negative Covid test prior to my visit. The ward I attended was supposed to be covid safe, however a patient on the ward would leave the ward to go to the ground floor to purchase food . The patient would then go and have a cigarette and come back to the ward  
This patient did this 3 times while I was there. Thank goodness I was a day case!  
This is NOT acceptable . Other patients were uncomfortable about this but afraid to say anything.  
The nursing staff seemed to be intimidated by this patient  
I just hope I do not contract Covid while I am recovering.&lt;/CommentText&gt;
